    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Lazo Arriaga</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 20th instant, accompanied by a copy of the treaty concluded at
                    the City of Mexico on April 1, 1895, between the Governments of Guatemala and
                    Mexico in settlement of their recent boundary dispute, and in which, by
                    direction of your Government, you convey an expression of its thanks for the
                    friendly interest manifested by the Government of the United States with a view
                    of preventing the continuation of a serious conflict between two neighboring
                    nations.</p>
                <p>I am happy, in reply, to express the gratification of the President, to whom I
                    have made known the contents of your note, that a peaceable settlement of the
                    differences that existed between the two Governments, alike honorable to both,
                    has thus been assured.</p>
                <p>Thanking you for the copy of the treaty, I take this occasion to renew, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
